life expectancy by 0.55 QALYs at an incremental cost-effectiveness ratio of 
$25,100 per QALY, as compared with aspirin. In poststroke patients, clopidogrel 
increased life expectancy by 0.17 QALYs at a cost of $31,200 per QALY. Aspirin 
was both less expensive and more effective than clopidogrel in post-myocardial 
infarction patients. In probabilistic sensitivity analyses, our evaluation for 
